|YKOWhen you are killed, you become a ghost and lose many of the
abilities you had while alive. Your spirit is whisked away to the
church of the land you died in, and your corpse - holding all of
your belongings and gold - travels with you in your inventory.

If you are level 5 or under, death carries no penalty at all.
Above level 5, death costs you 10% of your experience on hand.
Nothing else is lost: no stats, no levels.

To return to life, |YKB<pray>|YKO at the church (the experience loss
stands), or have another player resurrect you with a guild
ability, which restores the lost experience. Ghosts cannot pick
things up, so resurrect first, then unpack your corpse.

If you are somehow trapped as a ghost away from a church, the
|YKBgocot|YKO command will carry you to safety.

|WKBSee also: |YKBdeath, ghostemotes, deathavengement
